The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 March is 40,984 (4,743.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 March, there were 286 new confirmed cases (33.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 March, there were 322 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 11% (36 fewer cases).
